ile?language=EN>Hanley3</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/20/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>5:11:49 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/jmowrey/Han_Face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">A warning to those hunting in the Hole</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well, it was another happy night in the Hole, getting epic loot for our members...or so I thought.<br>
<br>
We had only gotten to the 1st dropoff and I was pulling that house when I came across the Scalekeeper. I conned him, was blue (52) and dubious, but I had heard about his insane lifetap (turns out it's 2500hp), so we decided to leave him alone and proceed to the SK, ranger, and chanter mobs. <br>
<br>
So, we start killing a golem in the dropoff area (outside the jails) and BAM...the Scalekeeper aggros and wipes out 18 ppl fast. <br>
<br>
We CR, move back down past him, and proceed past the pond and a couple courtyards away. Understand, he is nowhere near at this point, so we start haphazardly killing mobs that stand between us and glory, when BAMMMM--aggro, dead. Luckily a cleric camped, so we did the little rogue drag thing and rezzed our groups in. <br>
<br>
I decided (was my raid, unfortunately) to train him way the fook away from us, so I pulled a golem, DA, and ran by him. I proceeded to train him all the way out to the docks, where CERTAINLY we'd be safe. Heh, no. Within 5-10 pulls he just bolted at us from nowhere, no AE, no bard songs, nothing.<br>
<br>
So, the 3rd time was the charm and we left the zone. This seems very silly to take an already ridiculously aggro zone and add this element. He aggros when you kill the multitude of golems, but leaves you alone otherwise (unless you accidently attack him *cough* Awulfie). <br>
<br>
And...we petitioned, of course, only to hear that it would be brought to the attention of a GM. <br>
<br>
So, I just thought I'd warn you fine ppl to beware of the Hole until they fix this. We have trounced through that zone many times and rarely had much more than a death or two. Sorry to Learoy, Beltran, and Fardarter for being denied their epic drops (Fardarter's last piece). At least we got 2 Granite Spaulders and a pair of Loam Panty-looms.<br>
<br>
